:''This page covers blood types, quality and the Blood Pool. For the castle resource, see [[Blood Essence]]; for boss blood, see [[V Blood Carriers|V Blood]]; for the night event, see [[Blood Moon]]; for drinkable blood, see [[Blood Potion]].''
<blockquote>''"You will slowly lose health and ultimately perish if you run out of blood."''</blockquote>[[File:Frail Blood Pool.png|alt=Frailed|thumb|Example of a Frail Type Blood Pool; no bonuses.|400x400px]]Blood is a key resource in V Rising.

The player must continuously find new victims lest they run out of blood entirely. Feeding on a blood-carrying target (victim) will refill the player's Blood Pool to its maximum capacity of 10 liters and absorb the victim's blood type (Creature, Rogue, Warrior, etc.). Later on in the game the player unlocks {{ItemFrame|Blood Potion}} and {{ItemFrame|Blood Merlot}}, which allows them to store blood for later consumption. Each blood type provides different passive bonuses, with higher quality blood granting stronger bonuses. The 5 tiers of Blood Pool powers are unlocked at different percentage levels. For example, Tier IV Blood Pool powers will only be unlocked by draining a 90%+ blood quality victim.

The Blood Pool drains slowly over time, and faster when dealing & taking damage or using particular [[abilities#Vampire Powers|vampire powers]] such as {{Ability|Blood Mend}} or {{Ability|Expose Vein}}. Dying will immediately incur a 1 liter Blood Pool loss. Blood drainage can be virtually paused whilst sleeping in a [[Coffin]]. Blood drain is reduced by 25% on Relaxed Difficulty.<br>Upon running out of a non-frailed Blood Pool, the player's Blood Pool will revert to 1 liter of [[File:BloodType_Frailed.png|frameless|25px]] '''Frailed''' blood. <br>If their frailed Blood Pool runs out, the player's health will slowly deplete to 1 health. Feeding on any source of blood will restore the player's health regeneration.

Prior to v1.0, a player's current Blood Pool could not be refilled by any means. However, as of update 1.0, it is now possible by feeding on a defeated [[Primal Blood Soul]], either from a Tier 2 [[Rift Incursion]] in the [[Ruins of Mortium]] or a summoned one from the {{ItemFrame|Stygian Summoning Circle|type=Structure}}. Doing so will refill the player's current Blood Pool by 5 liters (50%).

