===Threshold Percentages===
Blood Quality % required to unlock each Tier<br>
*'''I''': '''&nbsp;&nbsp;1%'''
*'''II''': '''30%'''
*'''III''': '''60%'''
*'''IV''': '''90%'''
*'''V''': '''100%'''

===Bonus Scaling===
For tiers I - III, at least one variable is proportional to the quality of the given blood, down to a minimum of half the max potential bonus. For example, [[File:BloodType_Worker.png|frameless|30px]] Worker Blood's '''Tier 1''' bonus will provide at least '''12%''' but up-to '''24%''' Increased Resource yield, the value of which ranges between 1% and 100% Blood Quality:&nbsp;
*'''1%''' Blood Quality => '''12%''' Increased Resource yield
*'''30%''' Blood Quality => '''15.6%''' Increased Resource yield
*'''50%''' Blood Quality => '''18%''' Increased Resource yield
*'''99%''' Blood Quality => '''24%''' Increased Resource yield
*'''100%''' Blood Quality => '''~29%''' Increased Resource yield (including '''Tier V''' bonus of '''+20%''')

===Detecting Blood Types===
[[File:Blood Hunger Example.png|thumb|Example of the Blood Hunger ability with the blood type icon and percentage displayed.]]Mouse over a victim to display the blood type and blood quality percentage. See [[Enemies]] for a list of all enemies with a blood type.

Once the player has fed on the [[V Blood Carrier]] [[Tristan the Vampire Hunter]], they will unlock the {{Ability|Blood Hunger}} ability. Blood Hunger places the player in a blood detection mode, displaying the blood type icon and percentage over all victims' heads, instead of needing to mouse over.

==Blood Consumables==
The player can consume items such as {{ItemFrame|Rat}}s and {{ItemFrame|Tainted Heart}}s to restore a small amount of their blood pool, at the cost of changing their blood type to 'frailed', losing all blood type bonuses.

Once the player has fed on the [[V Blood Carrier]] [[Vincent the Frostbringer]], they will unlock {{ItemFrame|Prison Cell|type=Structure}}s. By using the {{Ability|Dominate}} Vampire Power they can imprison high-quality human victims and repeatedly extract {{ItemFrame|Blood Potion}}s / {{ItemFrame|Blood Merlot}}s from them. Allowing for a consistent supply of high quality blood.

Once the player has fed on [[Lucile the Venom Alchemist]], they will additionally be able to mix {{ItemFrame|Blood Potion}}s via the {{ItemFrame|Blood Homogenizer|type=Structure}}. This allows for fusing one of the blood traits in a potion into another. If&nbsp;the&nbsp;[[Blood#Blood Types & Quality|blood quality]] of the secondary potion is 90% or higher, the '''IV''' bonus will also be infused.

==Servants==
Servants increase in power and effectiveness with blood quality level. For more info see [[Servants]]. 

